cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CR 

The paper proposes a neural network model for anomaly detection, which falls under the category of machine learning. Specifically, the model uses deep networks to extract progressively rich representation of data, which suggests the paper could belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper applies the model to complex data sets like CIFAR and PFAM, which are image and protein sequence datasets respectively, indicating the paper could also belong to the sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also mentions the use of one-class objective, which is a common approach in anomaly detection, suggesting the paper could belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
